			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Drilling sludge is an oily, loose material from produced water that often ends up in water storage tanks. It can contain TENORM that is captured as liquid and gas passes through. It may remain in solution or settle out to form sludges that accumulate in tanks and pits, or form mineral scales inside pipes and drilling equipment. The biological treatment techniques of oily sludge are mainly cultivating, composting and sludge bioreactor, which use microorganisms to degrade petroleum hydrocarbons in the oil sludge into harmless soil composition.</common:generalComment>
